args: Let us waste no time in beginning our\ninvestigation. We must discover where\nour serial bloodsucker lurks.
I'm afraid we haven't a single clue so far.
Surely you're not without at least\nSOME information?
Just the reports of those harmed\nin the incidents so far.
They all claim the perpetrator\nwas dressed as a vampire.
Yes, though it's unclear why they would\ngo to the effort.
Unless it isn't a costume at all.
Ha ha ha! Gimme a break, lady.\nVampires only exist in spooky stories.
Heh heh. I suppose you have me there.\nThankfully, I have another theory...
The perpetrator is a human who wishes\nto be SEEN as a vampire.
I'm all for folks flying their freak flag,\nbut are vampire wannabes even a thing?
The world is full of people who desire to\nbe different from everyone else—and to\nbe both feared and respected.
It would scarce surprise me to find\nsomeone yearning to become a fearsome\nand spectacular beast of legend.
The desire to change oneself is common\nenough, but you think this person actually\nwants to incite fear?
If that's the case, they're likely to act out\nin ever more extreme ways in the future.
We have to find them before they put\nsomeone at real risk.
Sooooo what's the plan? We wander\naround looking for somebody dressed\nup with their teeth hangin' out?
I propose a simpler solution: Let us\nencourage the perpetrator to show\nthemselves willingly.
I don't think Dr. Bitey's just gonna\naccept an invitation, Akasha.
Then perhaps this calls for a\ndevilish little trick. Heh heh heh...
Barely made it in time for Halloween,\nbut we're finally here!
Good thing, too! This is the only time'a\nyear we make coin sellin' rotted pumpkins!
Plus I've always wanted to see everybody\ndressed up in costumes like they do here.
Hot pot of coffee, look at this welcoming\ncommittee! I TOLD ya Alberia is the best!\nThey sent a dame in a vampire costume!
Whatever do you mean, my dear?\nThis is no costume.
Uh, buddy? Maybe we oughta steer clear\nof this gal? She's kinda creepin' me out...
Mmm, what a wild imagination you have.\nNow won't you join me for the evening's\nrevels?
Poor, sleepless little lamb. I'll gladly\ncuddle until you fall into a deep and\nsoundless slumber...
Are you a...a vampire? You feel so...\nso warm and cozy...
I'm afraid we're getting more and more\nreports of townspeople saying they've\nseen a vampire, {player_name}.
Sounds like our perp is on the move!
Er, no. It's not that. Um...
Eyyy, Akasha! Lookin' gorgeous as always!\nCome sink those chompers in my neck!
For heaven's sake, show some decorum!\n...Also, I'M first!
I'm a little scared, but if it's Akasha\ndoing the biting, then...
You're looking more radiant than ever,\nmy dear vampire lady...
Heh heh. No need to fight over me,\ndarlings. Form a line and I'll see to\neach and every one of you in turn.
...So yes, I'm afraid Akasha managed to\nseduce the entire town.
In a single night?\nJust what did she do?
It's like she's a real vampire! Ha ha ha!
Mind your words, Notte, or you're liable\nto make the actual vampires jealous.
Hey, yeah! That guy was mixed in with\nthe crowd, but he wasn't swooning over\nAkasha like all the rest.
Quite the opposite, in fact—he seemed\nrather displeased by the whole scene.
Almost as if he didn't take kindly to me\nbeing called a vampire and being made\nthe center of attention.
Mmm. Our perpetrator is attempting to use\nthe guise of a vampire to stand out.
Surely such a person would find another\nvampire stealing their limelight to be\nunwelcome in the extreme.
Perhaps even enough for them to emerge\nfrom hiding so they might size up the\ncompetition firsthand.
Dude, look at the big brain on YOU!\nSo boyo over there is our guy, then?
It's too early to be certain, but it\nseems a lead worthy of following.
Pretty impressive stuff, Akasha.\nLet's follow him!
